				<section class="comment post-content">
					<div class="comment-text"><p>That’s a good point, Emlyna. I believe that the author isn’t saying that those are qualities that <i>must</i> be included in the Strong Female Lead™, but that if those are qualities embedded in the character to not forego them and turn her into a damsel in distress, a token cheerleader or a reward for the protagonist. That being said, I completely agree that there are many other ways for a woman to show strength other than brute force/physcially.</p>
</div>				</section>

